LinkedGeoData transforms geographic data from OpenStreetMap into RDF format, making it available as Linked Data. The dataset is generated and curated by citizens through the OpenStreetMap project, allowing users to query and use open spatial data for a variety of applications such as urban planning and geospatial analysis

This dataset maps citizen science initiatives in Latvia. It includes information on projects where citizens actively participate in data collection and analysis across various research areas. The mapping exercise was conducted as part of an Open Science study commissioned by the Latvian Ministry of Education and Science.

Dataset brief description: This dataset contains study assessing the satisfaction of users of the Occupational Health Service of the Madrid City Council, focusing on user profiles, satisfaction with medical check-ups, likelihood of recommending the service, compliance with service commitments, and collecting user feedback for service improvements.

Dataset name: Crime Sexual Assault by Chicago Data Portal
Dataset brief description: This dataset reflects reported incidents of crime (with the exception of murders where data exists for each victim) that occurred in the City of Chicago from 2001 to present.

Dataset name: Regional Datasets for Air Quality Monitoring in European Cities
Dataset brief description: This dataset provides hourly spatiotemporal data on air quality, weather, and land use in three European cities from 2020 to 2023, with a spatial resolution of 0.005 degrees.

Dataset name: Estudio de satisfacción de la ciudadanía con el Servicio de Cita Prev
Dataset brief description: This dataset contains the results of a satisfaction survey conducted to assess the experiences of users with the 'Cita Previa' appointment scheduling service offered by the Comunidad de Madrid, providing insights into the efficiency, user-friendliness, and overall satisfaction with the service.
